367 //Accepting protocol details from PROTOCOL DEV program:
368 void US_ExperimentMain::accept_passed_protocol_details( QMap < QString, QString > & protocol_details )
369 {
370  reset();
371 
372  qDebug() << "PROTOCOL DEV MODE !!!: ";
373  us_prot_dev_mode = true;
374 
375  QString pname = protocol_details[ "protocolName" ];
376  int invID_passed = protocol_details[ "invID_passed" ].toInt();
377 
378  qDebug() << "In US_Exp: Protocol Name: " << protocol_details[ "protocolName" ];
379  qDebug() << "In US_Exp: InvID: " << protocol_details[ "invID_passed" ];
380 
381  //Now, load passed protocol with enabling ONLY 8. AProfile && 9. Submit tab
382  US_Passwd pw;
383  QString masterPW = pw.getPasswd();
384  US_DB2 db( masterPW );
385 
386  if ( db.lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK )
387  {
388  QMessageBox::warning( this, tr( "Connection Problem" ),
389  tr( "Read protocol: Could not connect to database \n" ) + db.lastError() );
390  return;
391  }
392 
393  //Important: set investigator in US_Settings!!!
394  QStringList query;
395  query << "get_person_info" << protocol_details[ "invID_passed" ];
396  db.query( query );
397  db.next();
398 
399  QString firstName = db.value( 0 ).toString();
400  QString lastName = db.value( 1 ).toString();
401 
402  QString s = lastName + ", " + firstName;
403  US_Settings::set_us_inv_name( s );
404  US_Settings::set_us_inv_ID( invID_passed );
405 
406  QString inv_text = invID_passed + ": " + US_Settings::us_inv_name();
407  currProto.investigator = inv_text;
408  solutions_change = true;
409 
410  //re-read protocol list for current investigator
411  QList< QStringList > protocolsdata;
412  QStringList new_protlist;
413  US_ProtocolUtil::list_all( protocolsdata, &db );
414 
415  for ( int ii = 0; ii < protocolsdata.count(); ii++ )
416  new_protlist << protocolsdata[ ii ][ 0 ];
417 
418  setProtos( new_protlist );
420 
421  QString xmlstr( "" );
422  int protoID = US_ProtocolUtil::read_record_auto( pname, invID_passed, &xmlstr, NULL, &db );
423 
424  //le_protocol->setText( pname );
425  currProto.protoID = protoID;
426  loadProto.protoID = protoID;
427 
428  // Now that we have a protocol XML, convert it to internal controls
429  QXmlStreamReader xmli( xmlstr );
430  loadProto.fromXml( xmli );
431  loadProto.protoID = protoID;
432 
433  // Initialize the current protocol from the loaded one; set temperature
434  currProto = loadProto;
435  epanGeneral -> loaded_proto = 1;
436 
437  qDebug() << "In load_protocol: currProto.investigator 1 -- " << currProto.investigator;
438 
439  //set runName && label straight from the autoflow record:
440  currProto.runname = protocol_details[ "experimentName" ];
441  currProto.exp_label = protocol_details[ "label" ];
442 
443  initPanels();
444 
445  qDebug() << "In load_protocol: currProto.investigator 2 -- " << currProto.investigator;
446 
447  //SET epanAProf->sdiag->loadProf TO epanAProf->sdiag->currProf
448  US_AnaProfile aprof_curr_read = *(get_aprofile());
449  set_loadAProf ( aprof_curr_read );
450 
451  //Making Read-only
452  set_tabs_buttons_readonly();
453 
454  //copy protocol details params
455  protocol_details_passed.clear();
456  protocol_details_passed = protocol_details;
457 
458  emit close_expsetup_msg();
459 }

482 //re-initialize respectively AProfile's report/reportItem portions
483 void US_ExperimentMain::abde_sv_mode_change_reset_reports( QString exptype )
484 {
485  bool abde_mode = ( exptype == "ABDE" ) ? true : false;
486  qDebug() << "in abde_sv_mode_change_reset_reports(): abde_mode ?" << abde_mode;
487 
488  //Aprofile
489  US_AnaProfile* aprof = get_aprofile();
490 
491  //deal with general report sets
492 
493 
494  //deal with ch_reports
495  QMap< QString, QMap < QString, US_ReportGMP > >::iterator ri;
496 
497  for ( ri = aprof->ch_reports.begin(); ri != aprof->ch_reports.end(); ++ri )
498  {
499  QString chan_desc = ri.key();
500 
501  QMap < QString, US_ReportGMP > triple_reports = ri.value();
502  QMap < QString, US_ReportGMP >::iterator tri;
503  for ( tri = triple_reports.begin(); tri != triple_reports.end(); ++tri )
504  {
505  QString c_wvl = tri.key();
506 
507  epanAProfile->sdiag->currProf.ch_reports[ chan_desc ] [ c_wvl ].report_changed = false;;
508  epanAProfile->sdiag->currProf.ch_reports[ chan_desc ] [ c_wvl ].exp_time_changed = false;
509  epanAProfile->sdiag->currProf.ch_reports[ chan_desc ] [ c_wvl ].DBread = false;
510  epanAProfile->sdiag->currProf.ch_reports[ chan_desc ] [ c_wvl ].interf_report_changed = false;
511 
512  epanAProfile->sdiag->currProf.ch_reports[ chan_desc ] [ c_wvl ].reportItems.clear();
513  US_ReportGMP::ReportItem initItem;
514  initItem.type = ( abde_mode ) ? QString("Radius") : QString("s");
515  initItem.method = ( abde_mode ) ? QString("raw") : QString("2DSA-IT");
516 
517  qDebug() << "type, method -- " << initItem.type << ", " << initItem.method;
518  initItem.range_low = ( abde_mode ) ? 5.8 : 3.2;
519  initItem.range_high = ( abde_mode ) ? 7.0 : 3.7;
520  initItem.integration_val = 0.57;
521  initItem.tolerance = 10;
522  initItem.total_percent = 95;
523  initItem.combined_plot = 1;
524  initItem.ind_combined_plot = 1;
525 
526  epanAProfile->sdiag->currProf.ch_reports[ chan_desc ] [ c_wvl ].reportItems.push_back( initItem );
527 
528  }
529  }
530 }

789 // Return detail information for a specific centerpiece as named
790 bool US_ExperGuiGeneral::centpInfo( const QString cpname,
791  US_AbstractCenterpiece& cpEntry )
792 {
793  bool is_found = false;
794 
795  for ( int ii = 0; ii < acp_list.count(); ii++ )
796  { // Search abstract centerpieces for a name match
797  if ( acp_list[ ii ].name == cpname )
798  { // Match found: flag found and return entry
799  is_found = true;
800  cpEntry = acp_list[ ii ];
801  break;
802  }
803  }
804 
805  return is_found;
806 }

829 bool US_ExperGuiGeneral::updateProtos( const QStringList prentry )

840 // Verify valid label name (possible modify for valid-only characters)
841 void US_ExperGuiGeneral::label_name_entered( void )
842 {
843  QString lname = le_label->text();
844  QString old_lname = lname;
845  bool changed = false;
846 
847  /*** ALEXEY: RegExp COMMENTED OUT for now ****************************************/
848  /*
849  QRegExp rx( "[^A-Za-z0-9_-]" );
850  lname.replace( rx, "_" ); //ALEXEY - we may use alpha-numeric only, but not nessessarily..

852  if ( lname != old_lname )
853  { // Report on invalid characters replaced

884 // Verify valid run name (possible modify for valid-only characters)
885 void US_ExperGuiGeneral::run_name_entered( void )
886 {
887 DbgLv(1) << "EGGe: rchg: IN";
888  // Modify run name to have only valid characters
889  QRegExp rx( "[^A-Za-z0-9_-]" );
890  QString rname = le_runid->text();
891  QString old_rname = rname;
892 DbgLv(1) << "EGGe: rchg: old_rname" << old_rname;
893  rname.replace( rx, "_" );
894 DbgLv(1) << "EGGe: rchg: rname" << rname;
895  bool changed = false;
896 
897  if ( rname != old_rname )
898  { // Report on invalid characters replaced
899  QMessageBox::warning( this,
900  tr( "RunID Name Changed" ),
901  tr( "The runID name has been changed. It may consist only\n"
902  "of alphanumeric characters or underscore or hyphen.\n"
903  "New runID:\n " )
904  + rname );
905  changed = true;
906  }
907 
908 DbgLv(1) << "EGGe: rchg: len(runname)" << rname.length();
909  // Limit run ID length to 50 characters
910  if ( rname.length() > 50 )
911  {
912  QMessageBox::warning( this,
913  tr( "RunID Name Too Long" ),
914  tr( "The runID name may be at most\n"
915  "50 characters in length." ) );
916  rname = rname.left( 50 );
917  changed = true;
918  }
919 DbgLv(1) << "EGGe: rchg: changed" << changed;
920 
921  if ( changed )
922  { // Replace runID in line edit box
923  le_runid->setText( rname );
924  currProto->runname = rname;
925  }
926 
927  check_runname();

1038 // Load Protocol
1039 void US_ExperGuiGeneral::load_protocol( void )
1040 {
1041  bool fromdisk = US_Settings::debug_match( "protocolFromDisk" );
1042  bool load_db = fromdisk ? false : use_db;
1043  US_Passwd pw;
1044  QString xmlstr( "" );
1045  QStringList hdrs;
1046  int prx;
1047  QString pdtitle( tr( "Select a Protocol to Load" ) );
1048  pdtitle += ( ( load_db ) ?
1049  tr( " from Database" ) :
1050  tr( " from Disk" ) );
1051 //*DEBUG: forced input from disk
1052 if(fromdisk) {
1053 QString mtitle = tr( "Debug Forced Protocol from Disk" );
1054 QString message = tr( "The ability to load a protocol from the database\n" )
1055  + tr( "has been overridden by a debug setting.\n" )
1056  + tr( "Protocols from local disk will be listed." );
1057 QMessageBox::information( this, mtitle, message );
1058 }
1059 //*DEBUG: forced input from disk
1060 DbgLv(1) << "EGGe:ldPro: Disk-B: load_db" << load_db;
1061  // Get database connection pointer (or NULL as disk flag)
1062  US_DB2* dbP = load_db ? new US_DB2( pw.getPasswd() ) : NULL;
1063  int protoID = 0;
1064 
1065  // Build dialog table widget headers
1066  hdrs << "Protocol Name"
1067  << "Created"
1068  << ( load_db ? "DbID" : "File Name" );
1069 
1070  // Select a protocol
1071  QString delete_button = "DELETE";
1072  //US_SelectItem pdiag( protdata, hdrs, pdtitle, &prx, -2 );
1073  US_SelectItem* pdiag = new US_SelectItem( protdata, hdrs, pdtitle, &prx, delete_button, -2 ); //ALEXEY <-- with Delete button and functionality
1074 
1075  connect( pdiag, SIGNAL( accept_deletion() ), this, SLOT( update_protdata() ));
1076 
1077  if ( pdiag->exec() == QDialog::Accepted )
1078  { // Accept in dialog: get selected protocol name and its XML
1079  DbgLv(1) << "EGGe:ldPro: ACCEPT prx" << prx << "sel proto" << protdata[prx][0] << "protID" << protdata[prx][2];
1080 
1081  qDebug() << "In load_protocol: before RESET, currProto->investigator: -- " << currProto->investigator;
1082  //ALEXEY: need to reset everything:
1083  mainw->reset();
1084  qDebug() << "In load_protocol: after RESET, currProto->investigator: -- " << currProto->investigator;
1085 
1086  QString pname = protdata[ prx ][ 0 ];
1087 
1088  // Get the protocol XML that matches the selected protocol name
1089  protoID = US_ProtocolUtil::read_record( pname, &xmlstr, NULL, dbP );
1090 DbgLv(1) << "EGGe:ldPro: ACCEPT read_record return len(xml)" << xmlstr.length()
1091  << "protoID" << protoID;
1092 
1093  le_protocol->setText( pname );
1094  mainw->currProto.protoID = protoID;
1095  mainw->loadProto.protoID = protoID;
1096  }
1097 
1098  else
1099  { // Reject in dialog
1100 DbgLv(1) << "EGGe:ldPro: REJECT";
1101  return;
1102  }
1103 
1104  // Now that we have a protocol XML, convert it to internal controls
1105  QXmlStreamReader xmli( xmlstr );
1106  mainw->loadProto.fromXml( xmli );
1107  mainw->loadProto.protoID = protoID;
1108 
1109  // Initialize the current protocol from the loaded one; set temperature
1110  mainw->currProto = mainw->loadProto;
1111  ct_tempera->setValue( mainw->currProto.temperature );
1112  ct_tedelay->setValue( mainw->currProto.temeq_delay );
1113  //ALEXEY: set Project name
1114  le_project->setText ( mainw->currProto.project );
1115 
1116 DbgLv(1) << "EGGe:ldPro: dur0" << mainw->currProto.rpSpeed.ssteps[0].duration;
1117 DbgLv(1) << "EGGe:ldPro: cPname" << mainw->currProto.protoname
1118  << "lPname" << mainw->loadProto.protoname << "pdbID" << mainw->loadProto.protoID;
1119 DbgLv(1) << "EGGe:ldPro: cOhost" << mainw->currProto.optimahost
1120  << "lOhost" << mainw->loadProto.optimahost;
1121 DbgLv(1) << "EGGe:ldPro: cTempe" << mainw->currProto.temperature
1122  << "lTempe" << mainw->loadProto.temperature;
1123 
1124  QString rname = le_runid->text();
1125  if ( !rname.isEmpty() )
1126  mainw->currProto.runname = rname;
1127  loaded_proto = 1;
1128 
1129  //if ABDE protocol, or NOT
1130  if ( mainw->currProto.rpRotor.exptype == "Buoyancy" )
1131  {
1132  mainw-> set_abde_mode_aprofile();
1133  mainw-> abde_sv_mode_change_reset_reports( "ABDE" );
1134  }
1135  else
1136  {
1137  mainw->unset_abde_mode_aprofile();
1138  mainw-> abde_sv_mode_change_reset_reports( "SV" );
1139  }
1140 
1141  // Initialize all other panels using the new protocol
1142 
1143  qDebug() << "In load_protocol: currProto->investigator 1 -- " << currProto->investigator;
1144 
1145  mainw->initPanels();
1146  // If there is a linked AnalysisProfile, copy to loadAProto!!!
1147  //SET epanAProf->sdiag->loadProf TO epanAProf->sdiag->currProf
1148  US_AnaProfile aprof_curr_read = *(mainw->get_aprofile());
1149  mainw->set_loadAProf ( aprof_curr_read );
1150 
1151  qDebug() << "In load_protocol: currProto->investigator 2 -- " << currProto->investigator;
1152 
1153  check_runname();
1154 }

1216 // Get centerpiece information (initially or after DB/Disk change
1217 void US_ExperGuiGeneral::centerpieceInfo( void )
1218 {
1219  US_Passwd pw;
1220  US_DB2* dbP = use_db ? new US_DB2( pw.getPasswd() ) : NULL;
1221 
1222  // Read in the full centerpiece information from DB or Disk
1223  US_AbstractCenterpiece::read_centerpieces( dbP, acp_list );
1224  cp_names.clear();

1613 
1614  }

1619  }
1620  }

1661 
1662 // Import from disk
1663 void US_ExperGuiRotor::importDisk( void )
1664 {
1665  QString dir;
1666  int jmpType = 0;
1667 
1668  dir = QFileDialog::getExistingDirectory( this,
1669  tr( "Raw Data Directory" ),
1670  US_Settings::importDir(),
1671  QFileDialog::DontResolveSymlinks );
1672 
1673  dir.replace( "\\", "/" );
1674 
1675  if ( dir.isEmpty() ) // If no directory chosen, return now
1676  return;
1677 
1678  QDir readDir( dir, "*", QDir::Name, QDir::Files | QDir::Readable );
1679  readDir.makeAbsolute();
1680  if ( dir.right( 1 ) != "/" ) dir += "/"; // Ensure trailing "/"
1681 
1682  //Now, infer triples from the raw data being uploaded
1683  QStringList nameFilters = QStringList( "*.auc" );
1684  QStringList files = readDir.entryList( nameFilters,
1685  QDir::Files | QDir::Readable, QDir::Name );
1686  //check for .auc presence
1687  if ( files. size() == 0 )
1688  {
1689  QMessageBox::warning( this,
1690  tr( "NO .AUC DATA DETECTED!" ),
1691  tr( "No .auc data detected in the selected directory... \n"
1692  ));
1693  return;
1694  }
1695 
1696  //set currentDir
1697  importDataPath = dir;
1698 
1699  //clear all internals
1700  isMwl = false;
1701  allData .clear();
1702  all_tripinfo. clear();
1703  runTypes_map. clear();
1704  channs_ranges.clear();
1705  unique_runTypes. clear();
1706  run_details .clear();
1707  ra_data_type = false;
1708  ra_data_sim = false;
1709  ck_absorbance_t ->setChecked( false );
1710 
1711  for ( int trx = 0; trx < files.size(); trx++ )
1712  {
1713  QString fname = files[ trx ];
1714  QString fpath = dir + fname;
1715 
1716  US_DataIO::RawData rdata;
1717  US_Convert::TripleInfo tripinfo;
1718 
1719  // Get a raw data from an auc file
1720  US_DataIO::readRawData( fpath, rdata );
1721 
1722  // Save the raw data for this triple
1723  allData << rdata;
1724 
1725  // Save triple information
1726  QString triple = QString::number( rdata.cell ) + " / "
1727  + QString( rdata.channel ) + " / "
1728  + QString::number( qRound( rdata.scanData[ 0 ].wavelength ) );
1729 
1730  qDebug() << "triple # trx -- " << triple;
1731  if ( triple. contains("/ S /") )
1732  {
1733  if ( qRound( rdata.scanData[ 0 ].wavelength ) == 0 )
1734  {
1735  QMessageBox::critical( this,
1736  tr( "ERROR: SIMULATED DATA WAVELENGTH" ),
1737  tr( "Uploaded simulated data not generated correctly:\n\n"
1738  "Wavelength: 0\n\n"
1739  "Please upload correctly generated simulated data, or raw data in .auc format."
1740  ));
1741  return;
1742  }
1743 
1744  ra_data_sim = true;
1745  triple = triple.replace("/ S /","/ A /");
1746  }
1747 
1748  tripinfo.tripleID = trx + 1;
1749  tripinfo.tripleDesc = triple;
1750  tripinfo.description = rdata.description;
1751  tripinfo.channelID = trx + 1;
1752  tripinfo.tripleFilename = fname;
1753 
1754  all_tripinfo << tripinfo;
1755 
1756  //Now runTypes
1757  QString runType_t = QString( fname ).section( ".", -5, -5 );
1758  QString channumber = tripinfo.tripleDesc.split(" / ")[0].simplified();
1759  runTypes_map[ channumber ] << runType_t;
1760  unique_runTypes << runType_t;
1761  }
1762 
1763  QString fname_1 = files[ 0 ];
1764  runType = QString( fname_1 ).section( ".", -5, -5 );
1765  runID = QString( fname_1 ).section( ".", 0, -6 );
1766 
1767  //Remove duplicates in runTypes_map
1768  unique_runTypes .removeDuplicates();
1769  //first, uncheck "absorbance" type
1770  if ( !ck_absorbance_t->isChecked() )
1771  ck_absorbance_t ->setChecked( false );
1772  //next, check if "RA" (and only) type, set checked
1773  qDebug() << "unique_runTypes -- " << unique_runTypes;
1774  if ( unique_runTypes.size() == 1 && unique_runTypes[0] == "RA")
1775  {
1776  ck_absorbance_t ->setChecked( true );
1777  ra_data_type = true;
1778  }
1779 
1780  for (int i=0; i<runTypes_map.keys().size(); ++i )
1781  {
1782  runTypes_map[ runTypes_map.keys()[i] ].removeDuplicates();
1783  if ( ra_data_type )
1784  {
1785  runTypes_map[ runTypes_map.keys()[i] ].clear();
1786  runTypes_map[ runTypes_map.keys()[i] ] << "RI";
1787  }
1788  qDebug() << "Channel: " << runTypes_map.keys()[i]
1789  << ", types: " << runTypes_map[ runTypes_map.keys()[i] ];
1790  }
1791 
1792  //End triples inquiry
1793 
1794  //Before building protocol, check for correct ROTOR
1795  if ( !rotorForUploadedData() )
1796  {
1797  //msg
1798  QMessageBox::critical( this,
1799  tr( "NOTE: Rotor not Selected Correctly!" ),
1800  tr( "Rotor does not match, please select a different rotor!" ) );
1801 
1802  //clean
1803  importDataPath = "";
1804  le_dataDiskPath -> setText("");
1805  ck_absorbance_t -> setChecked( false );
1806  ra_data_type = false;
1807  ra_data_sim = false;
1808 
1809  isMwl = false;
1810  allData .clear();
1811  all_tripinfo. clear();
1812  runTypes_map. clear();
1813  channs_ranges.clear();
1814  unique_runTypes. clear();
1815  run_details .clear();
1816 
1817  importDisk_cleanProto();
1818 
1819  //return
1820  return;
1821  }
1822 
1823 
1824  //Build protocol based on read-in channels, triples, ranges...
1825  channs_ranges = build_protocol_for_data_import( runTypes_map );
1826 
1827  //Maybe insert informing dialog (on channels, ranges)??
1828  QString msg_wvls;
1829  for( int i=0; i<channs_ranges.keys().size(); ++i )
1830  {
1831  QString ch_c = channs_ranges.keys()[ i ];
1832 
1833  if ( ra_data_type && ch_c. contains("B") )
1834  continue;
1835 
1836  QString o_types = runTypes_map[ ch_c.left(1) ]
1837  . join(",")
1838  . replace("RI","UV/vis.")
1839  . replace("IP","Interf.");
1840  msg_wvls += ch_c;
1841

1843  QString wvl_min, wvl_max;
1844  int wvl_count;
1845  if ( !wvls.isEmpty() )
1846  {
1847  wvl_min = wvls[0];
1848  wvl_max = wvls[wvls.size() - 1];
1849  wvl_count = wvls.size();
1850 
1851  msg_wvls += "; #wvls: " + QString::number(wvl_count) + " (from " + wvl_min + " to " + wvl_max + ")";
1852  }
1853  msg_wvls += "; optics: " + o_types + "<br>";
1854  }
1855 
1856  //Run Details
1857  QString msg_run_details = run_details["RPM"] + " RPM; ";
1858  int run_duration = run_details["Time"].toInt();
1859  int rd_hours = (int)qFloor( run_duration / 3600.0 );
1860  int rd_mins = (int)qRound( ( run_duration - rd_hours * 3600.0 ) / 60.0 );
1861  QString hh = "h";
1862  QString rd_str = QString().sprintf( "%d %s %02d m", rd_hours, hh.toLatin1().data(), rd_mins );
1863  msg_run_details += rd_str + "; ";
1864  QString scanCount = run_details["ScanCount"];
1865  msg_run_details += scanCount;
1866 
1867  //Sim/Raw ?
1868  QString data_sim_raw = ( ra_data_sim ) ? "Simulated" : "Raw";
1869 
1870 
1871  //msg box
1872  QMessageBox * msg_dataRead = new QMessageBox(this);
1873  msg_dataRead->setIcon(QMessageBox::Information);
1874  msg_dataRead->setWindowTitle(tr("%1 Data from Disk Read").arg( data_sim_raw ));
1875  msg_dataRead->setText(tr( "%1 data from disk uploaded!<br><br>"
1876  "The following information was identified and propagated into the current protocol:<br><br>"
1877  "<b>Rotor Speed / Run Length / {Data Type: #Scans}</b><br>"
1878  "<b>%2</b><br><br>"
1879  "<b>Channels / Ranges / Optics:</b><br>"
1880  "<b>%3</b><br>"
1881  "<font color='red'><b>NOTE:</b></font> "
1882  "This information will be cleared and regenerated upon new data-from-disk, or the protocol upload."
1883  )
1884  .arg( data_sim_raw )
1885  .arg( msg_run_details )
1886  .arg( msg_wvls )
1887  );
1888 
1889  msg_dataRead->exec();
1890 
1891  //set up dir path
1892  le_dataDiskPath ->setText( importDataPath );
1893 }

1895 //Check for rotor fpr uploaded data
1896 bool US_ExperGuiRotor::rotorForUploadedData()
1897 {
1898  bool isRotor = true;
1899 
1900  int nholes = sibIValue( "rotor", "nholes" );
1901  QStringList chann_list;
1902  for( int i=0; i< all_tripinfo.size(); ++i)
1903  {
1904  QString channumber = all_tripinfo[i].tripleDesc.split(" / ")[0].simplified();
1905  chann_list << channumber;
1906  }
1907  chann_list. removeDuplicates();
1908 
1909  for( int i=0; i< chann_list.size(); ++i)
1910  {
1911  int chann_number = chann_list[i].toInt();
1912  if ( chann_number > nholes )
1913  {
1914  isRotor = false;
1915  break;
1916  }
1917  }
1918 
1919  return isRotor;
1920 }

1924 bool US_ExperGuiRotor::init_output_data()
1925 {
1926  bool success = true;
1927  bool have_trip = ( all_tripinfo.size() == allData.size() );
1928  qDebug() << "[in init_output_data()]: have_trip" << have_trip;
1929  if ( ! have_trip )
1930  all_tripinfo.clear();
1931  outData .clear();
1932  all_chaninfo.clear();
1933  all_triples .clear();
1934  all_channels.clear();
1935  out_tripinfo.clear();
1936  out_chaninfo.clear();
1937  out_triples .clear();
1938  out_channels.clear();
1939  out_chandatx.clear();
1940 
1941  // Set up initial export-data pointers list and all/out lists
1942  for ( int trx = 0; trx < allData.size(); trx++ )
1943  {
1944  US_DataIO::RawData* edata = &allData[ trx ];
1945  US_Convert::TripleInfo tripinfo;
1946  US_Convert::TripleInfo chaninfo;
1947 
1948  outData << edata;
1949 
1950  if ( have_trip )
1951  tripinfo = all_tripinfo[ trx ];
1952 
1953  char chtype[ 3 ] = { 'R', 'A', '\0' };
1954  strncpy( chtype, allData[ trx ].type, 2 );
1955  QString dataType = QString( chtype ).left( 2 );
1956  qDebug() << "dataType -- " << dataType;
1957

1959  + QString( edata->channel ) + " / "
1960  + ( ! runType.contains( "W" )
1961  ? QString::number( qRound( edata->scanData[ 0 ].wavelength ) )
1962  : tripinfo.tripleDesc.section( " / ", 2, 2 ) );
1963  QString celchn = triple.section( " / ", 0, 1 );
1964  int chanID = all_channels.indexOf( celchn ) + 1;
1965  chanID = ( chanID < 1 ) ? ( all_channels.count() + 1 ) : chanID;
1966  tripinfo.tripleID = trx + 1;
1967  tripinfo.tripleDesc = triple;
1968  tripinfo.description = edata->description;
1969  tripinfo.channelID = chanID;
1970  tripinfo.tripleFilename = dataType;
1971  tripinfo.excluded = false;
1972  chaninfo = tripinfo;
1973  chaninfo.tripleDesc = celchn;
1974 DbgLv(1) << "CGui:IOD: trx" << trx << "triple" << triple;
1975 
1976  if ( have_trip )
1977  all_tripinfo[ trx ] = tripinfo;
1978  else
1979  all_tripinfo << tripinfo;
1980  out_tripinfo << tripinfo;
1981  all_triples << triple;
1982  out_triples << triple;
1983 
1984  if ( ! all_channels.contains( celchn ) || runType.contains( "W" ) )
1985  {
1986  all_channels << celchn;
1987  all_chaninfo << chaninfo;
1988  out_channels << celchn;
1989  out_chaninfo << chaninfo;
1990  out_chandatx << trx;
1991 DbgLv(1) << "CGui:IOD: ochx" << trx << "celchn cID" << celchn << chanID;
1992  }
1993  }
1994 
1995  // Save a vector of speed steps read or computed from the data scans
1996  char chtype[ 3 ] = { 'R', 'A', '\0' };
1997  strncpy( chtype, allData[ 0 ].type, 2 );
1998  QString dataType = QString( chtype ).left( 2 );
1999  int nspeed = US_SimulationParameters::readSpeedSteps( runID, dataType,
2000  speedsteps );
2001  int nspeedc = 0;
2002  bool low_accel = false;
2003  double rate = 400.0;
2004 DbgLv(1) << "CGui:IOD: rSS nspeed" << nspeed;
2005 
2006  if ( nspeed == 0 )
2007  { // Compute speed steps from all raw auc data
2008  US_SimulationParameters::computeSpeedSteps( allData, speedsteps );
2009  nspeedc = speedsteps.size();
2010  nspeed = nspeedc;
2011 DbgLv(1) << "CGui:IOD: cSS nspeed" << speedsteps.size();
2012 
2013  // Check to see if implied 1st acceleration is too low
2014 #define DSS_LO_ACC 250.0 // default SetSpeedLowAccel
2015  // if ( impType != 2 ) // Check if not imported AUC
2016  // {
2017  // QString dbgval = US_Settings::debug_value( "SetSpeedLowAcc" );
2018  // double ss_lo_acc = dbgval.isEmpty() ? DSS_LO_ACC : dbgval.toDouble();
2019  // low_accel = US_AstfemMath::low_acceleration( speedsteps, ss_lo_acc, rate );
2020  // }
2021  }
2022 
2023  // Report problematic 1st speed step
2024  if ( low_accel )
2025  {
2026  int tf_scan = speedsteps[ 0 ].time_first;
2027  int accel1 = (int)qRound( rate );
2028  int rspeed = speedsteps[ 0 ].rotorspeed;
2029  double tf_aend = static_cast<double>(tf_scan);
2030  // prevent any division by zero
2031  if (accel1 != 0)
2032  {
2033  tf_aend = static_cast<double>(rspeed) / static_cast<double>(accel1);
2034  }
2035 
2036  QString wmsg = tr( "The SpeedStep computed/used is likely bad:<br/>"
2037  "The acceleration implied is %1 rpm/sec.<br/>"
2038  "The acceleration zone ends at %2 seconds,<br/>"
2039  "with a first scan time of %3 seconds.<br/><br/>"
2040  "<b>You should rerun the experiment without<br/>"
2041  "any interim constant speed, and then<br/>"
2042  "you should reimport the data.</b>" )
2043  .arg( accel1 ).arg( QString::number(tf_aend) ).arg( QString::number(tf_scan) );
2044 
2045  QMessageBox msgBox( this );
2046  msgBox.setWindowTitle( tr( "Bad TimeState Implied!" ) );
2047  msgBox.setTextFormat( Qt::RichText );
2048  msgBox.setText( wmsg );
2049  msgBox.addButton( tr( "Continue" ), QMessageBox::RejectRole );
2050  QPushButton* bAbort = msgBox.addButton( tr( "Abort" ),
2051  QMessageBox::YesRole );
2052  msgBox.setDefaultButton( bAbort );
2053  msgBox.exec();
2054  if ( msgBox.clickedButton() == bAbort )
2055  { // Abort the import of this data
2056  QApplication::restoreOverrideCursor();
2057  qApp->processEvents();
2058  //reset();
2059  return false;
2060  }
2061  else
2062  { // Modify times and omegas of this data, then proceed to import
2063  int status = US_Convert::adjustSpeedstep( allData, speedsteps );
2064 DbgLv(1) << "CGui:IOD: adjSS stat" << status;
2065  }
2066  }
2067 
2068  // MultiWaveLength if channels and triples counts differ
2069  isMwl = ( all_chaninfo.count() != all_tripinfo.count() );
2070  if ( isMwl && ( all_tripinfo.count() / all_chaninfo.count() ) < 4 )
2071  { // If less than 4 wavelengths, treat as non-MWL
2072  isMwl = false;
2073  all_chaninfo = all_tripinfo;
2074  out_chaninfo = out_tripinfo;
2075  out_chandatx.clear();
2076 
2077  for ( int jj = 0; jj < out_tripinfo.count(); jj++ )
2078  out_chandatx << jj;
2079 DbgLv(1) << "CGui:IOD: isMwl" << isMwl << "ac.count at.count oc.count"
2080  << all_chaninfo.count() << all_tripinfo.count() << out_chaninfo.count();
2081  }
2082 
2083  if ( isMwl )
2084  { // If MWL, update speed steps
2085 DbgLv(1) << "CGui:IOD: updSS call";
2086  QVector< SP_SPEEDPROFILE > testss = speedsteps;
2087  int nstest = mwl_data.update_speedsteps( testss );
2088  if ( nstest > 0 )
2089  {
2090  nspeed = nstest;
2091  speedsteps = testss;
2092  }
2093  else if ( nstest < 0 )
2094  {
2095  QMessageBox::critical( this,
2096  tr( "Invalid MWL Speedsteps" ),
2097  tr( "The \"set_speed\" values in MWRS files have"
2098  " resulted in too many speed steps or steps"
2099  " where speeds decrease.\n\nImport is ABORTED!!" ) );
2100  success = false;
2101  //resetAll();
2102  }
2103 DbgLv(1) << "CGui:IOD: updSS nspeed nstest nspeedc"
2104  << nspeed << nstest << nspeedc << "ss0 timf omgf"
2105  << speedsteps[0].time_first << speedsteps[0].w2t_first;
2106  }
2107 
2108  else
2109  { // Else complete channel lists
2110  for ( int trx = 0; trx < all_tripinfo.count(); trx++ )
2111  {
2112  QString triple = all_tripinfo[ trx ].tripleDesc;
2113 DbgLv(1) << "CGui:IOD: trx" << trx << "triple" << triple;
2114  all_chaninfo[ trx ].tripleDesc = triple;
2115  out_chaninfo[ trx ].tripleDesc = triple;
2116  }
2117 DbgLv(1) << "CGui:IOD: nspeed" << nspeed << "sp0.rspeed sp0.avspeed"
2118  << nspeed << speedsteps[0].rotorspeed << speedsteps[0].avg_speed;
2119  }
2120 
2121 DbgLv(1) << "CGui:IOD: RETURN";
2122  return success;
2123 }

2768 // Slot for rotor,calibration changed in advanced dialog
2769 void US_ExperGuiRotor::advRotorChanged( US_Rotor::Rotor& crotor,
2770  US_Rotor::RotorCalibration& ccalib )
2771 {
2772  int rID = crotor.ID;
2773  int cID = ccalib.ID;
2774  int rx = -1;
2775 DbgLv(1) << "EGR: advRChg: new rID cID" << rID << cID;
2776 
2777  for ( int ii = 0; ii < sl_rotors.count(); ii++ )
2778  { // Find and select the list item matching the accepted rotor
2779  int eID = sl_rotors[ ii ].section( ":", 0, 0 ).toInt();
2780  if ( eID == rID )
2781  { // Match: select item, set index, break from loop
2782  cb_rotor ->setCurrentIndex( ii );
2783  rx = ii;
2784 DbgLv(1) << "EGR: advRChg: rID match at index" << ii;
2785  break;
2786  }
2787  }
2788 
2789  if ( rx >= 0 )
2790  changeRotor( rx ); // Rebuild calibrations for new rotor
2791 
2792  for ( int ii = 0; ii < sl_calibs.count(); ii++ )
2793  { // Find and select the list item matching the accepted calibration
2794  int eID = sl_calibs[ ii ].section( ":", 0, 0 ).toInt();
2795  if ( eID == cID )
2796  {
2797  cb_calibr->setCurrentIndex( ii );
2798 DbgLv(1) << "EGR: advRChg: cID match at index" << ii;
2799  break;
2800  }
2801 DbgLv(1) << "EGR: advRChg: ii eID" << ii << eID;
2802  }
2803 }

2805 // Function to return the abstract rotor for the current rotor
2806 US_Rotor::AbstractRotor* US_ExperGuiRotor::abstractRotor( const QString rotor )
2807 {
2808 DbgLv(1) << "EGR: absR: rotor" << rotor;
2809  int arID = -1;
2810  for ( int ii = 0; ii < rotors.count(); ii++ )
2811  { // Search for a match to the rotor name
2812 DbgLv(1) << "EGR: absR: ii" << ii << "rname" << rotors[ii].name;
2813  if ( rotors[ ii ].name.trimmed() == rotor )
2814  { // Match found: break with abstractRotor ID value
2815 
2816  qDebug() << "ABSTROT: ROTOR INFO !!!!: " << rotors[ ii ].name << ", "
2817  << rotors[ ii ].abstractRotorID << ", " << rotors[ ii ].labID << ", "
2818  << rotors[ ii ].serialNumber;
2819  arID = rotors[ ii ].abstractRotorID;
2820  break;
2821  }
2822  }
2823 DbgLv(1) << "EGR: arID" << arID << "arcount" << arotors.count();
2824  for ( int ii = 0; ii < arotors.count(); ii++ )
2825  { // Search for a match to the abstract rotor ID
2826 DbgLv(1) << "EGR: absR: ii" << ii << "rID" << arotors[ii].ID;
2827  if ( arotors[ ii ].ID == arID )
2828  { // Match found: return with pointer to abstract rotor object
2829  return ( &arotors[ ii ] );
2830  }
2831  }
2832 
2833  return NULL;
2834 }

3290 // Return speed profile description string for an indicated step
3291 QString US_ExperGuiSpeeds::speedp_description( int ssx )
3292 {
3293  // For example: "Speed Profile 1: 30000 rpm for 5 hr 30 min"

3295  //double durhr = qFloor( durtim / 60.0 ); // Duration hours

3297  // double durmin = durtim - ( durhr * 60.0 ); // Duration residual minutes
3298  double durmin = (durtim / 60.0) - ( durhr * 60.0 ); // Duration residual minutes
3299 
3300  //int escans = qRound( durtim * 6.0 ); // Estimated step scans //ALEXEY: 6 scans per minute ???
3301  //int escans = qRound( (durtim / 60.0) * 6.0 ); // Estimated step scans //ALEXEY: 6 scans per minute ???
3302 
3303  //Uv-vis
3304  //double scaninterval = ssvals[ ssx ][ "scanintv" ]; //ALEXEY: ssval[]["scanintv"] is set (in secs) according to table: RPM vs scanint
3305  //int escans = qRound( durtim / scaninterval );
3306  double scaninterval_min = ssvals[ ssx ][ "scanintv_min" ]; //Use minimum scanint instead (always)
3307  int escans = qRound( durtim / scaninterval_min );
3308  //interference
3309  double scaninterval_int = ssvals[ ssx ][ "scanintv_int" ];
3310  int escans_int = qRound( durtim / scaninterval_int );
3311 
3312

3314  int tscans_int = 0;
3315  for ( int ii = 0; ii < ssvals.size(); ii++ )
3316  {
3317  tscans += qRound( ssvals[ ii ][ "duration" ] / ssvals[ ii ][ "scanintv" ] ); //ALEXEY bug fixed
3318  tscans_int += qRound( ssvals[ ii ][ "duration" ] / ssvals[ ii ][ "scanintv_int" ] );
3319  }
3320  qDebug() << "SCAN INT: " << scaninterval_min << ", # Scans: " << tscans;
3321 
3322 
3323  // return tr( "Speed Profile %1 : %2 rpm for %3 hr %4 min"
3324  // " (%5 estimated scans, %6 run total)" )
3325  // .arg( ssx + 1 ).arg( ssvals[ ssx ][ "speed" ] )
3326  // .arg( durhr ).arg( durmin ).arg( escans ).arg( tscans );
3327 
3328  return tr( "Speed Profile %1 : %2 rpm for %3 hr %4 min"
3329  " Maximum # of scans possible: %5 (UV-vis, total), %6 (Interference, per cell)" )
3330  .arg( ssx + 1 ).arg( ssvals[ ssx ][ "speed" ] )
3331  .arg( durhr ).arg( durmin ).arg( escans ).arg( escans_int );

3602 //Set ScanInt based on RPM speed entered
3603 void US_ExperGuiSpeeds::ssChangeScInt( double val, int row )
3604 {
3605  // Fit of the time-interval graph with A0 + A1/X; [X => val]
3606  QVector<double> a0(4);
3607  QVector<double> a1(4);
3608  a0[0] = 5.3513; a1[0] = 167308; // rpm 3000 - 14000:
3609  a0[1] = 5.66431; a1[1] = 329920; // rpm 15000 - 32000:
3610  a0[2] = 6.16695; a1[2] = 480761; // rpm 33000 - 50000:
3611  a0[3] = 4.44766; a1[3] = 744728; // rpm 51000 - 60000:
3612 
3613  double time_scint;
3614  if (val <= 14999 )
3615  time_scint = a0[0] + qRound( a1[0]/val );
3616  if (val >= 15000 and val <= 32999 )
3617  time_scint = a0[1] + qRound( a1[1]/val );
3618  if (val >= 33000 and val <= 50999 )
3619  time_scint = a0[2] + qRound( a1[2]/val );
3620  if (val >= 51000 and val <= 60000 )
3621  time_scint = a0[3] + qRound( a1[3]/val );
3622 
3623  ssvals[row]["scanintv"] = time_scint;
3624  ssvals[row]["scanintv_min"] = time_scint;
3625 
3626  QList< int > hms_scint;
3627  US_RunProtocol::timeToList( time_scint, hms_scint );
3628 
3629  // not needed here as these will overwrite current counters when another speed profile is added. Values set in ChProfile function.
3630  // sb_scnint_hh ->setMinimum( (int)hms_scint[ 1 ] );
3631  // sb_scnint_mm ->setMinimum( (int)hms_scint[ 2 ] );
3632  // sb_scnint_ss ->setMinimum( (int)hms_scint[ 3 ] );
3633 
3634  // sb_scnint_hh ->setValue( (int)hms_scint[ 1 ] );
3635  // sb_scnint_mm ->setValue( (int)hms_scint[ 2 ] );
3636  // sb_scnint_ss ->setValue( (int)hms_scint[ 3 ] );
3637 
3638  scanint_ss_min[row] = (int)hms_scint[ 3 ];
3639  scanint_mm_min[row] = (int)hms_scint[ 2 ];
3640  scanint_hh_min[row] = (int)hms_scint[ 1 ];
3641 
3642  qDebug() << "ScanInt: " << ssvals[row]["scanintv"];
3643 
3644  //interference: do not change default minimum values (from us_run_protocol.ccp SpeedStep.scanintv_int)
3645  double default_interval_int = 5.0;
3646  ssvals[row]["scanintv_int"] = default_interval_int; // rpSpeed->ssteps[0].scanintv_int;
3647  ssvals[row]["scanintv_min_int"] = default_interval_int; // rpSpeed->ssteps[0].scanintv_int;
3648 
3649  QList< int > hms_scint_int;
3650  US_RunProtocol::timeToList( default_interval_int, hms_scint_int );
3651 
3652  scanint_ss_int_min[row] = (int)hms_scint_int[ 3 ];
3653  scanint_mm_int_min[row] = (int)hms_scint_int[ 2 ];
3654  scanint_hh_int_min[row] = (int)hms_scint_int[ 1 ];
3655 }

3672 /*Scan # Estimator *****************************************************************************/
3673 void US_ExperGuiSpeeds::ssChgWvlPerCell( int val )
3674 {
3675  int tot_wvl = val;
3676  double duration_sec = ssvals[ curssx ][ "duration" ]; //ssteps[ i ].duration;
3677  double scanint_sec = ssvals[ curssx ][ "scanintv" ]; //ssteps[ i ].scanintv;
3678  double scanint_sec_min;
3679  std::modf (ssvals[ curssx ][ "scanintv_min" ], &scanint_sec_min);
3680 
3681  int scancount = 0;
3682 
3683  //ALEXEY: use this algorithm to calculate scanCount && scanInt
3684  if ( scanint_sec > scanint_sec_min*tot_wvl )
3685  scancount = int( duration_sec / scanint_sec );
3686  else
3687  scancount = int( duration_sec / (scanint_sec_min * tot_wvl) );
3688 
3689  le_scans_per_cell -> setText( QString::number( scancount ));
3690 }

3693 /* DURATION ***********************************************************************************/
3694 // Slot for change in duration time (hours)
3695 void US_ExperGuiSpeeds::ssChgDuratTime_hh( int val )
3696 {
3697  double ssdurday = (double)sb_durat_dd->value();
3698  double ssdurhr = val;
3699  double ssdurmin = (double)sb_durat_mm->value();
3700  double ssdursec = (double)sb_durat_ss->value();
3701  double ssdurtim = ( ssdurday * 3600.0 * 24 ) + ( ssdurhr * 3600.0 ) + ( ssdurmin * 60.0 ) + ssdursec;
3702 
3703  ssvals[ curssx ][ "duration" ] = ssdurtim; // Set Duration in step vals vector
3704 
3705  profdesc[ curssx ] = speedp_description( curssx );
3706  cb_prof->setItemText( curssx, profdesc[ curssx ] );
3707 
3708  qDebug() << "Time in sec aftes HH changed: " << ssdurtim;
3709 
3710  // Set total time
3711  QList< int > hms_tot;
3712  double ssdurtim_d = ssdurtim + ssvals[ curssx ][ "delay_stage" ];
3713  ssvals[ curssx ][ "total_time" ] = ssdurtim_d;
3714  US_RunProtocol::timeToList( ssdurtim_d, hms_tot );
3715  QString tot_str = QString::number( hms_tot[ 0 ] ) + "d " + QString::number( hms_tot[ 1 ] ) + "h " + QString::number( hms_tot[ 2 ] ) + "m ";
3716  le_total_time->setText( tot_str );
3717 
3718  //Set Scan # in estimator
3719  int tot_wvl = (int)sb_wvl_per_cell->value();
3720  double duration_sec = ssvals[ curssx ][ "duration" ]; //ssteps[ i ].duration;
3721  double scanint_sec = ssvals[ curssx ][ "scanintv" ]; //ssteps[ i ].scanintv;
3722  // double scanint_sec_min = ssvals[ curssx ][ "scanintv_min" ]; //ssteps[ i ].scanintv_min;
3723  double scanint_sec_min;
3724  std::modf (ssvals[ curssx ][ "scanintv_min" ], &scanint_sec_min);
3725 
3726  int scancount = 0;
3727  if ( scanint_sec > scanint_sec_min*tot_wvl )
3728  scancount = int( duration_sec / scanint_sec );
3729  else
3730  scancount = int( duration_sec / (scanint_sec_min * tot_wvl) );
3731 
3732  le_scans_per_cell -> setText( QString::number( scancount ));
3733 }

3861 void US_ExperGuiSpeeds::ssChgScIntTime_hh( int val )
3862 {

3876  {
3877  sb_scnint_mm->setMinimum(0);
3878  sb_scnint_ss->setMinimum(0);
3879  }
3880  if ( val == minimum_hh )
3881  {
3882  if ( ssscintmin <= minimum_mm )
3883  {
3884  sb_scnint_mm->setMinimum(minimum_mm);
3885  sb_scnint_mm->setValue(minimum_mm);

3887  sb_scnint_ss->setValue(minimum_ss);
3888 
3889  ssscintmin = (double)sb_scnint_mm->value(); // Bug fixed
3890  ssscintsec = (double)sb_scnint_ss->value();
3891  }
3892  }
3893 
3894  double ssscinttim = ( ssscinthr * 3600.0 ) + ( ssscintmin * 60.0 ) + ssscintsec;
3895  ssvals[ curssx ][ "scanintv" ] = ssscinttim; // Set ScInt in step vals vector
3896 
3897  profdesc[ curssx ] = speedp_description( curssx );
3898  cb_prof->setItemText( curssx, profdesc[ curssx ] );
3899 
3900  //Set Scan # in estimator

4270 //Slot to synchronize all stage delays with that for the 1st stage
4271 void US_ExperGuiSpeeds::stageDelay_sync( void )
4272 {
4273  double delay = ssvals[ 0 ][ "delay_stage" ]; //delay for the 1st stage in sec
4274 
4275  double delay_hh = qFloor( delay / 3600.0 ); // Delay in hh
4276  double delay_mm = (delay / 60.0) - ( delay_hh * 60.0 ); // Delay in min
4277 
4278  sb_delay_st_hh ->setValue( (int)delay_hh );
4279  sb_delay_st_mm ->setValue( (int)delay_mm );
4280 
4281  qDebug() << "IN STAGE SYNC: nspeed: " << nspeed;
4282  int tot_speeds = ssvals.size();
4283  for ( int i = 1; i < tot_speeds; i++ )
4284  {
4285  ssvals[ i ][ "delay_stage" ] = delay;
4286  }
4287 
4288 }
4289 
4290 void US_ExperGuiSpeeds::syncdelayChecked( bool checked )
4291 {
4292  if (checked)
4293  stageDelay_sync();
4294 }

4296 // Function to adjust delay minimum when related values are changed
4297 void US_ExperGuiSpeeds::adjustDelay( void )
4298 {
4299  // Set minimum delay time based on speed change and acceleration
4300  double cspeed = ssvals[ curssx ][ "speed" ]; // Current step's speed
4301  double pspeed = ( curssx > 0 ) ? ssvals[ curssx - 1 ][ "speed" ] : 0.0;
4302  double spdelta = fabs(cspeed - pspeed); // Speed delta <-- In case there is deceleration..
4303  double accel = ssvals[ curssx ][ "accel" ]; // Acceleration
4304 #warning "Check if this accel is guaranteed to be non-zero, inform user if it is zero?"
4305  double delaylow = qCeil( spdelta / accel ); // Low seconds delay
4306 
4307  //Uv-vis
4308  QList< int > dhms;
4309  double actual_delaylow = 2*60 + delaylow; // ALEXEY: Uv-vis delay = 2 mins + speed/accel;
4310  US_RunProtocol::timeToList( actual_delaylow, dhms );
4311  sb_delay_hh ->setValue( (int)dhms[ 1 ] );
4312 
4313  if ( (int)dhms[ 3 ] > 0 ) //ALEXEY round to nearest min.
4314  {
4315  if ( (int)dhms[ 2 ] == 0 )
4316  {
4317  sb_delay_mm->setMinimum(1);
4318  sb_delay_mm ->setValue(1);
4319  }
4320  if ( (int)dhms[ 2 ] > 0 )
4321  {
4322  sb_delay_mm->setMinimum( (int)dhms[ 2 ] + 1 );
4323  sb_delay_mm ->setValue( (int)dhms[ 2 ] + 1 );
4324  }
4325  }
4326  else
4327  {
4328  sb_delay_mm->setMinimum( (int)dhms[ 2 ] );
4329  sb_delay_mm ->setValue( (int)dhms[ 2 ] );
4330  }
4331  delay_mm_min[ curssx ] = sb_delay_mm->value();
4332 
4333  //interference
4334  QList< int > dhms_int;
4335  double actual_delaylow_int = 6*60 + delaylow; // ALEXEY: Interference delay = 6 mins + speed/accel;
4336  US_RunProtocol::timeToList( actual_delaylow_int, dhms_int );
4337  sb_delay_int_hh ->setValue( (int)dhms_int[ 1 ] );
4338 
4339  if ( (int)dhms_int[ 3 ] > 0 ) //ALEXEY round to nearest min.
4340  {
4341  if ( (int)dhms_int[ 2 ] == 0 )
4342  {
4343  sb_delay_int_mm->setMinimum(1);
4344  sb_delay_int_mm ->setValue(1);
4345  }
4346  if ( (int)dhms_int[ 2 ] > 0 )
4347  {
4348  sb_delay_int_mm->setMinimum( (int)dhms_int[ 2 ] + 1 );
4349  sb_delay_int_mm ->setValue( (int)dhms_int[ 2 ] + 1 );
4350  }
4351  }
4352  else
4353  {
4354  sb_delay_int_mm->setMinimum( (int)dhms_int[ 2 ] );
4355  sb_delay_int_mm ->setValue( (int)dhms_int[ 2 ] );
4356  }
4357  delay_mm_int_min[ curssx ] = sb_delay_int_mm->value();
4358 
4359 }

4436 // Function to rebuild the Cells protocol after Rotor change
4437 void US_ExperGuiCells::rebuild_Cells( void )
4438 {
4439  int nholes = sibIValue( "rotor", "nholes" );
4440 DbgLv(1) << "EGCe:rbC: r_nholes" << nholes << "c_ncell" << rpCells->ncell;
4441  if ( nholes == rpCells->ncell )
4442  return; // No rotor change means no rebuild
4443 
4444  if ( rpCells->ncell == 0 )
4445  { // No existing Cells protocol, so initialize a brand-new one
4446 DbgLv(1) << "EGCe:rbC: ++NEW Cell protocol++";
4447  rpCells->ncell = nholes;
4448  rpCells->nused = 0;
4449  rpCells->used.clear();
4450  return;
4451  }
4452 
4453  // Otherwise, construct a protocol based on rotor holes
4454  if ( nholes < rpCells->ncell )
4455  { // Decreasing cells count: Recompute used count
4456 DbgLv(1) << "EGCe:rbC: H<C: nused" << rpCells->nused;
4457  int kused = 0;
4458  for ( int ii = 0; ii < rpCells->nused; ii++ )
4459  {
4460  if ( rpCells->used[ ii ].cell > nholes )
4461  break;
4462  kused++;
4463 DbgLv(1) << "EGCe:rbC: ii" << ii << "kused" << kused;
4464  }
4465 
4466  //rpCells->nused = kused; // Resize used-cells vector
4467  //rpCells->used.resize( kused );
4468 
4469  rpCells->nused = 0; // ALEXEY: # used cells should be 0 when Rotor
4470  rpCells->used.clear(); // ALEXEY: no used cells when rotor is changed - otherwise cells are not populated correcly
4471  }
4472  else
4473  { // If cells count increases, same as above: clear used, i.e. make all fresh-empty, and counterbalance (empty-counterbalance)
4474  rpCells->nused = 0; // ALEXEY: # used cells should be 0 when Rotor
4475  rpCells->used.clear(); // ALEXEY: no used cells when rotor is changed - otherwise cells are not populated correcly
4476  }
4477 
4478 
4479  rpCells->ncell = nholes; // Reset total cells count up/down
4480 DbgLv(1) << "EGCe:rbC: ncell" << nholes;
4481 }

4483 // Slot for change in centerpiece selection
4484 void US_ExperGuiCells::centerpieceChanged( int sel )
4485 {
4486 DbgLv(1) << "EGCe:cpChg: sel" << sel;
4487  QObject* sobj = sender(); // Sender object
4488  QString sname = sobj->objectName();
4489  int irow = sname.section( ":", 0, 0 ).toInt();
4490 DbgLv(1) << "EGCe:cpChg: sname irow" << sname << irow;
4491  int nholes = sibIValue( "rotor", "nholes" );
4492  int icbal = nholes - 1; // Counter-balance index
4493 
4494  if ( irow != icbal )
4495  { // Not counterbalance: change cross cell
4496  int halfnh = nholes / 2; // Half number holes
4497  int xrow = ( irow < halfnh ) ? irow + halfnh : irow - halfnh;
4498  int jsel = sel; // Use same centerpiece for cross
4499 DbgLv(1) << "EGCe:cpChg: xrow icbal" << xrow << icbal;
4500 
4501  if ( xrow == icbal )
4502  {
4503  if ( cc_cenps[ xrow ]->currentText().contains( tr( "counterbalance" ) ) )
4504  { // Cross cell is counterbalance
4505  jsel = 1; // Usually "Beckman counterbalance"
4506  QString cpname = cc_cenps[ irow ]->currentText();
4507  DbgLv(1) << "EGCe:cpChg: cpname" << cpname << "tcb_centps" << tcb_centps;
4508  if ( tcb_centps.contains( cpname ) )
4509  jsel = 2; // In some cases "Titanium counterbalance"
4510  }
4511  else
4512  {
4513  jsel = sel + 3; //ALEXEY plus 3 since cent. list is longer in counterbalance rows
4514  }
4515  }
4516 
4517 DbgLv(1) << "EGCe:cpChg: CB:jsel" << jsel;
4518  cc_cenps[ xrow ]->setCurrentIndex( jsel );
4519  }
4520  else //ALEXEY: if index of the counterbalance - treat when NOT counterbalance
4521  {
4522  QString cpname_counter = cc_cenps[ irow ]->currentText();
4523  if ( ! cpname_counter.contains( tr( "counterbalance" ) ) )
4524  {
4525  cc_winds[ irow ]->setVisible( true );
4526  //ALEXEY: change cross cell centerpiece (8->4, or 4->2)
4527  int halfnh_c = nholes / 2;
4528  int xrow_c = irow - halfnh_c;
4529  int jsel_c = sel - 3; // Use same centerpiece for cross (minus 3 since cent. list is longer in counterbalance rows)
4530 
4531  cc_cenps[ xrow_c ]->setCurrentIndex( jsel_c );
4532 
4533  // Set windows
4534  if ( cc_winds[ xrow_c ]->currentText().contains( tr( "quartz" ) ) )
4535  cc_winds[ irow ]->setCurrentIndex( 0 );
4536  else if ( cc_winds[ xrow_c ]->currentText().contains( tr( "sapphire" ) ) )
4537  cc_winds[ irow ]->setCurrentIndex( 1 );
4538  }
4539  else
4540  cc_winds[ irow ]->setVisible( false );
4541  }
4542 
4543 }
4544 
4545 // Slot for change in windows selection
4546 void US_ExperGuiCells::windowsChanged( int sel )
4547 {
4548 DbgLv(1) << "EGCe:wiChg: sel" << sel;
4549  QObject* sobj = sender(); // Sender object
4550  QString sname = sobj->objectName();

4555

4578  int halfnh_c = nholes / 2;

5037 // Return the solution object for a given solution description
5038 bool US_ExperGuiSolutions::solutionData( const QString sdescr,
5039  US_Solution& soludata )
5040 {
5041  QString solID = QString( "" );
5042  bool found = solutionID( sdescr, solID );
5043 DbgLv(1) << "EGSo:solDat: sdescr" << sdescr << "found" << found
5044  << "solID" << solID;
5045 
5046  if ( found )
5047  {
5048  if ( solu_data.keys().contains( sdescr ) )
5049  { // Previously fetched and mapped: just return it
5050  soludata = solu_data[ sdescr ];
5051 DbgLv(1) << "EGSo:solDat: OLDfound descr" << soludata.solutionDesc;
5052  }
5053 
5054  else
5055  { // Not fetched before: do so now and map it
5056  US_Passwd pw;
5057  US_DB2* dbP = ( sibSValue( "general", "dbdisk" ) == "DB" )
5058  ? new US_DB2( pw.getPasswd() ) : NULL;
5059  if ( dbP != NULL )
5060  {
5061  int stat = soludata.readFromDB( solID.toInt(), dbP );
5062  found = ( stat == US_DB2::OK );
5063 DbgLv(1) << "EGSo:solDat: NEWfound descr" << soludata.solutionDesc << stat;
5064  }
5065  else
5066  {
5067  soludata.readFromDisk( solID );
5068  }
5069  solu_data[ sdescr ] = soludata;
5070  }
5071  }
5072 
5073  return found;
5074 }

5076 // Build a mapping of all solution descriptions to solution IDs
5077 int US_ExperGuiSolutions::allSolutions()
5078 {
5079  sonames.clear();
5080  sonames << "(unspecified)";
5081  QStringList soids;
5082 
5083  qDebug() << "In allSolutions(), currProto->investigator 1 -- " << mainw->currProto.investigator;
5084 
5085  US_Passwd pw;
5086  US_DB2* dbP = ( sibSValue( "general", "dbdisk" ) == "DB" )
5087  ? new US_DB2( pw.getPasswd() ) : NULL;
5088 //DbgLv(1) << "EGSo: allSo: dbP" << dbP;
5089  if ( dbP != NULL )
5090  { // Read all the solutions in the database
5091  soids << "-1";
5092  QString invID = sibSValue( "general", "investigator" )
5093  .section( ":", 0, 0 ).simplified();
5094 
5095  qDebug() << "In allSolutions(), currProto->investigator 2 -- " << mainw->currProto.investigator;
5096  qDebug() << "In allSolutions(), invID -- " << invID; //ALEXEY: when inv changed, this sibSValue does NOT capture invID !!! needs correction...
5097 
5098 
5099  QStringList qry;
5100  qry << "all_solutionIDs" << invID;
5101  dbP->query( qry );
5102 
5103  if ( dbP->lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK )
5104  {
5105  qDebug() << "*ERROR* allSolutions error" << dbP->lastErrno();
5106  return 0;
5107  }
5108 
5109  while ( dbP->next() )
5110  {
5111  QString solID = dbP->value( 0 ).toString();
5112  QString descr = dbP->value( 1 ).toString();
5113 
5114  if ( descr.isEmpty() )
5115  continue;
5116 
5117  solu_ids[ descr ] = solID;
5118  sonames << descr;
5119  soids << solID;
5120  }
5121  } // END: solutions in DB
5122 
5123  else
5124  { // Read all the solutions on the local disk
5125  soids << "00000000";
5126  QString path;
5127  US_Solution solution;
5128  if ( ! solution.diskPath( path ) )
5129  return 0;
5130 
5131  QDir dir( path );
5132  QStringList filter( "S*.xml" );
5133  QStringList fnames = dir.entryList( filter, QDir::Files,
5134  QDir::Name );
5135  QString solID;
5136  QString descr;
5137 
5138  for ( int ii = 0; ii < fnames.size(); ii++ )
5139  { // Examine each S*.xml file
5140 DbgLv(1) << "EGSo: allSo: file" << (ii+1) << "of" << fnames.size() << fnames[ii];
5141  QFile* s_file = new QFile( path + "/" + fnames[ ii ] );
5142 
5143  if ( ! s_file->open( QIODevice::ReadOnly | QIODevice::Text ) )
5144  continue;
5145 
5146  QXmlStreamReader xmli( s_file );
5147 
5148  while ( ! xmli.atEnd() )
5149  {
5150  xmli.readNext();
5151 
5152  if ( xmli.isStartElement() )
5153  {
5154  QXmlStreamAttributes attrs = xmli.attributes();
5155 
5156  if ( xmli.name() == "solution" )
5157  {
5158  solID = attrs.value( "guid" ).toString();
5159  }
5160 
5161  else if ( xmli.name() == "description" )
5162  {
5163  xmli.readNext();
5164  descr = xmli.text().toString();
5165 
5166  if ( descr.isEmpty() )
5167  continue;
5168 
5169  solu_ids[ descr ] = solID;
5170  sonames << descr;
5171  soids << solID;
5172  }
5173  } // END: Start element
5174  } // END: XML element loop
5175 DbgLv(1) << "EGSo: allSo: desc" << descr << "solID" << solID;
5176  s_file->close();
5177  } // END: file names loop
5178 
5179 // s_file.close();
5180  } // END: solutions on local disk
5181 
5182  // Do a pass through solution names looking for duplicates
5183  int ndup = 0;
5184  for ( int ii = 1; ii < sonames.count(); ii++ )
5185  {
5186  QString sname = sonames[ ii ];
5187  int lstx = sonames.lastIndexOf( sname );
5188  if ( lstx > ii )
5189  { // At least one other with this name, make them unique
5190  ndup++;
5191  QString snbase = sname;
5192  int kk = 1;
5193  sname = snbase + QString().sprintf( " (%d)", kk );
5194  sonames.replace( ii, sname ); // Replace 1st of duplicates
5195  for ( int jj = ii + 1; jj <= lstx; jj++ )
5196  {
5197  sname = sonames[ jj ];
5198 
5199  if ( sname == snbase )
5200  { // This is a duplicate
5201  kk++;
5202  sname = snbase + QString().sprintf( " (%d)", kk );
5203  sonames.replace( jj, sname ); // Replace each of duplicates
5204  }
5205  }
5206  } // Handling duplicate
5207  } // Testing solution entries
5208 
5209  if ( ndup > 0 )
5210  { // There were duplicates, so re-do the name-to-id mapping
5211  solu_ids.clear();
5212  for ( int ii = 0; ii < sonames.count(); ii++ )
5213  {
5214  QString sname = sonames[ ii ];
5215  solu_ids[ sname ] = soids [ ii ];
5216  }
5217  } // Re-mapping ids to names
5218 DbgLv(1) << "EGSo: allSo: sids count" << solu_ids.keys().count();
5219 DbgLv(1) << "EGSo: allSo: sids keys --" << solu_ids.keys();
5220 
5221  return solu_ids.keys().count();
5222 }
5223 
5224 // Slot to handle click on row Add to Comments button
5225 void US_ExperGuiSolutions::addComments()
5226 {
5227 DbgLv(1) << "EGSo:addComm: IN";
5228  bool ok;
5229  QString chcomm( "" );
5230 
5231  QStringList comms;

5563 // Function to rebuild the Optical protocol after Solutions change
5564 void US_ExperGuiOptical::rebuild_Optic( void )
5565 {
5566 
5567 
5568  int nchanf = sibIValue( "solutions", "nchanf" );
5569  QStringList ochans = sibLValue( "solutions", "sochannels" );
5570  int kochan = ochans.count();

5574  {
5575  nochan = ochans.count();
5576  int ndiff = ( nochan == nchanf ) ? 0 : 1;
5577  nochan = qMin( nochan, nchanf );
5578 
5579  for ( int ii = 0; ii < nochan; ii++ )
5580  {
5581  if ( rpOptic->chopts[ ii ].channel != ochans[ ii ] )
5582  ndiff++;
5583  }
5584

5586  return; // No solutions change means no rebuild

5706 // Slot to handle an optical system being checked
5707 void US_ExperGuiOptical::opsysChecked( bool checked )
5708 {
5709 DbgLv(1) << "EGOp: oCk: checked" << checked;
5710  // Determine which row and which of 3 possible check boxes
5711  QObject* sobj = sender(); // Sender object
5712  QString oname = sobj->objectName();
5713  int irow = oname.section( ":", 0, 0 ).toInt();
5714  int ibtn = oname.mid( oname.length() - 1 ).toInt();
5715 DbgLv(1) << "EGOp: oCk: oname" << oname << "irow" << irow << "ibtn" << ibtn;
5716  // Ignore if not Interference
5717  QString optype = cc_osyss[ irow ]->button( ibtn )->text();
5718 DbgLv(1) << "EGOp: oCk: optype" << optype;
5719 
5720  // if ( optype != tr( "Rayleigh Interference" ) ) //ALEXEY: couple checkboxes for all optics
5721  // return;
5722 
5723  // If Interference, get a list of same-cell rows; disconnect
5724  QString clabl = cc_labls[ irow ]->text();
5725  QString scell = clabl.left( 1 );
5726  QString labnone = tr( "none" );
5727  QList< int > ccrows;
5728 DbgLv(1) << "EGOp: oCk: clabl" << clabl << "scell" << scell;
5729  for ( int ii = 0; ii < mxrow; ii++ )
5730  {
5731  // Ignore the exact same row
5732  if ( ii == irow )
5733  continue;
5734  // Get row label and quit loop when at end visible rows
5735  QString rlabl = cc_labls[ ii ]->text();
5736  if ( rlabl == labnone )
5737  break;
5738  // Compare the cell value to that of the one (un)checked
5739  QString rcell = rlabl.left( 1 );
5740  if ( rcell == scell )
5741  { // Save same-cell row and disconnect the checkbox
5742  ccrows << ii;
5743  cc_osyss[ ii ]->button( ibtn )->disconnect();
5744 DbgLv(1) << "EGOp: oCk: ii" << ii << "rlabl" << rlabl;
5745  }
5746  }
5747 DbgLv(1) << "EGOp: oCk: ccrows" << ccrows;
5748 
5749  // Set check-state of Interference boxes in same-cell rows and reconnect
5750  for ( int ii = 0; ii < ccrows.count(); ii++ )

5817 //Resize AnalysisProfile properly
5818 void US_ExperGuiAProfile::resizeEvent( QResizeEvent *event )
5819 {
5820  int upper_height = mainw->tabHeight + mainw->buttLHeight * 3 - 8;
5821  int new_main_w = mainw->width();
5822  int new_main_h = mainw->height() - upper_height;
5823 
5824  if ( new_main_w > sdiag->width() || new_main_h > sdiag->height())
5825  {
5826  int newWidth = qMax( new_main_w, sdiag->width() );
5827  int newHeight = qMax( new_main_h, sdiag->height() );
5828  sdiag->setMaximumSize( newWidth, newHeight );
5829  sdiag->resize( QSize( newWidth, newHeight ) );
5830  update();
5831  }
5832 
5833  if ( new_main_w < sdiag->width() || new_main_h < sdiag->height() )
5834  {
5835  int newWidth = qMin( new_main_w, sdiag->width() );
5836  int newHeight = qMin( new_main_h, sdiag->height() );
5837  sdiag->setMaximumSize( newWidth, newHeight );
5838  sdiag->resize( QSize( newWidth, newHeight ) );
5839  update();
5840  }
5841 
5842  QWidget::resizeEvent(event);
5843 }

6074 // Slot to show details of all experiment controls

6076 {
6077  // Create a new editor text dialog with fixed font
6078  US_Editor* ediag = new US_Editor( US_Editor::DEFAULT, true, "", this );

6082  US_GuiSettings::fontSize() - 1,

6085 DbgLv(1) << "EGUp:detE: ufont" << ufont.family();
6086  QApplication::setOverrideCursor( QCursor( Qt::WaitCursor ) );
6087 
6088  // Accumulate information on controls that have been specified
6089  QString v_invid = mainw->currProto.investigator;
6090  QString v_dbdisk = sibSValue( "general", "dbdisk" );
6091  QString v_run = mainw->currProto.runname;

6100  QString v_operID = QString::number(rpRotor->operID);
6101  QString v_instID = QString::number(rpRotor->instID);

6103

6574 // Slot to save the current Reports && fill out QMaps relating chdesc-to-reportID
6575 void US_ExperGuiUpload::saveReports( US_AnaProfile* aprof )
6576 {
6577  qDebug() << "Saving REPORTS !!!";
6578 
6579  //Clear ch_desc-to-ids/guid maps
6580  aprof->ch_report_guids.clear();
6581  aprof->ch_report_ids.clear();
6582 
6583 
6584  //Iterate over Reports
6585  //QMap<QString, US_ReportGMP>::iterator ri;
6586 
6587  //ALEXEY_NEW_REPORT:
6588  QMap< QString, QMap < QString, US_ReportGMP > >::iterator ri;
6589 
6590  for ( ri = aprof->ch_reports.begin(); ri != aprof->ch_reports.end(); ++ri )
6591  {
6592  //ALEXEY_NEW_REPORT:
6593  // now will be a cycle over channel's wvls:
6594  // ri.value() IS a QMap < QString( wvl ), US_ReportGMP >
6595  // iterate over this QMap's keys() == wavelengths
6596  // aprof->ch_report_ids[ ri.key() ][ i ] = reportID;
6597  // //Generate new Report GuiID:
6598  // aprof->ch_report_guids [ ri.key() ] = US_Util::new_guid();
6599 
6600  QString chan_desc = ri.key();
6601  QList< int > ch_reportIDs;
6602  QStringList ch_reportGUIDs;
6603 
6604  QMap < QString, US_ReportGMP > triple_reports = ri.value();
6605  QMap < QString, US_ReportGMP >::iterator tri;
6606 
6607  int triple_count = 0;
6608  for ( tri = triple_reports.begin(); tri != triple_reports.end(); ++tri )
6609  {
6610  QString curr_guid = US_Util::new_guid();
6611  ch_reportGUIDs << curr_guid;
6612 
6613  //Return new Report ID from DB insertion:
6614  int reportID = writeReportToDB( curr_guid, tri.value() );
6615  ch_reportIDs.push_back( reportID );
6616 
6617  qDebug() << "Report ID/GUID: triple -- "
6618  << ri.key() << ": " << tri.key()
6619  << " -- " << reportID << " / "
6620  << curr_guid;
6621 
6622  ++triple_count;
6623  //For ABDE case, stop after recording the 1st-in-channel report:
6624  if ( mainw->us_abde_mode && triple_count == 1 )
6625  {
6626  qDebug() << "Exiting GMP Report DB writing after the 1st triple in a channel...";
6627  break;
6628  }
6629  }
6630 
6631  //now, insert reportIDs && reportGUIDs for current channel:
6632  aprof->ch_report_guids [ chan_desc ] = ch_reportGUIDs;
6633  aprof->ch_report_ids [ chan_desc ] = ch_reportIDs;
6634  }
6635 }

6637 //Write a single Report to DB
6638 int US_ExperGuiUpload::writeReportToDB( QString reportGUID, US_ReportGMP report )
6639 {
6640  qDebug() << "Writing Report " << report.channel_name;
6641  int reportID = 0;
6642 
6643  US_DB2* dbP = NULL;
6644  US_Passwd pw;
6645  dbP = new US_DB2( pw.getPasswd() );
6646  if ( dbP->lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK )
6647  {
6648  QMessageBox::warning( this, tr( "Connection Problem" ),
6649  tr( "Saving Report: Could not connect to database: \n" ) + dbP->lastError() );
6650  return reportID;
6651  }
6652 
6653  //Copmose JSON string for report Mask first:
6654  QString jsonMask = QString("{");
6655 
6656  int tot_conc_bool = report.tot_conc_mask ? 1 : 0;

6658

6693

6892 // Slot to save the current Run Protocol
6893 bool US_ExperGuiUpload::saveRunProtocol()
6894 {
6895  bool save_aborted = false;
6896 
6897  qDebug() << "in saveRunProtoocl(): proto_svd, rps_differ -- " << proto_svd << rps_differ;
6898  if ( proto_svd && !rps_differ )
6899  {
6900  qDebug() << "Protocol already saved && not changed since that...";
6901  return save_aborted;
6902  }
6903 
6904  qDebug() << "Peoceed with Saving protocol!";
6905 
6906  if ( mainw->ScanCount_global > 1501 )
6907  {
6908  QMessageBox::critical( this,
6909  tr( "*ERROR* in Saving Protocol" ),
6910  tr( "UV/vis.: Protocol cannot be saved: \n"
6911  "Number of scans per cell per wavelengths is %1. \n"
6912  "It must not exceed 1501. \n\n"
6913  "Please revise experiment parameters accordingly." )
6914  .arg( mainw->ScanCount_global ) );
6915  return save_aborted;
6916  }
6917 
6918  if ( mainw->ScanCount_global_int > 1501 )
6919  {
6920  QMessageBox::critical( this,
6921  tr( "*ERROR* in Saving Protocol" ),
6922  tr( "Protocol cannot be saved: \n"
6923  "Interference: Number of scans per cell is %1. \n"
6924  "It must not exceed 1501. \n\n"
6925  "Please revise experiment parameters accordingly." )
6926  .arg( mainw->ScanCount_global_int ) );
6927  return save_aborted;
6928  }
6929 
6930 
6931 
6932 DbgLv(1) << "EGUp:svRP: IN";
6933  // Test that the current protocol name is new
6934  QStringList prnames;
6935  QList< QStringList > prdats;
6936 DbgLv(1) << "EGUp:svRP: call getProtos()";
6937  mainw->getProtos( prnames, prdats );
6938 DbgLv(1) << "EGUp:svRP: prnames" << prnames;
6939 
6940  QString protoname = sibSValue( "general", "protocol" );
6941 
6942  QString old_protoname = protoname;
6943 //DbgLv(1) << "EGUp:svRP: protoname" << protoname << "prdats0" << prdats[0]; //ALEXEY: important: this statement caused bug when no protocols existed in the DB
6944 
6945  if ( prnames.contains( protoname ) || protoname.trimmed().isEmpty() )
6946  { // Cannot save until a new protocol name is given
6947  QString mtitle = tr( "Protocol Name not New" );
6948  QString message = tr( "The current Run Protocol cannot be saved until\n"
6949  "a unique new name is given for it.\n\n"
6950  "In the dialog to follow, add a distinguishing\n"
6951  "suffix to the current protocol name/description\n"
6952  "or create a completely new description." );
6953  QMessageBox::critical( this, mtitle, message );
6954  }
6955  bool ok;
6956  QString newpname = protoname;
6957  QString msg =
6958  tr( "Enter a new Run Protocol name (description text)<br/>"
6959  "for the record to be saved; or modify the<br/>"
6960  "existing name so that it is unique.<br/><br/>"
6961  "Then click on <b>OK</b> to accept the new name<br/>"
6962  "or on <b>Cancel</b> to abort the Run Protocol save.<br/>" );
6963 
6964  // Keep displaying the dialog text until a unique name is given
6965  while( prnames.contains( newpname ) || newpname.trimmed().isEmpty() )
6966  {
6967  newpname = QInputDialog::getText( this,
6968  tr( "Enter New Run Protocol Name/Description" ),
6969  msg, QLineEdit::Normal, newpname, &ok );
6970 
6971  if ( ! ok )
6972  { // Cancel: abort the save
6973  QMessageBox::critical( this,
6974  tr( "Save Run Protocol Aborted" ),
6975  tr( "The save of a new Run Protocol record<br/>"
6976  "has been aborted." ) );
6977 
6978  save_aborted = true;
6979 
6980  return save_aborted;
6981  }
6982  }
6983 
6984  // //ALEXEY: check if has_interference or has_uvvis or both for cells//
6985  // QString uvvis = tr( "UV/visible" );
6986  // QString rayleigh = tr( "Rayleigh Interference" );
6987  // QStringList oprof = sibLValue( "optical", "profiles" );
6988 
6989 
6990 
6991  // Save the new name and compose the XML representing the protocol
6992  protoname = newpname;
6993 DbgLv(1) << "EGUp:svRP: NEW protoname" << protoname;
6994 DbgLv(1) << "EGUp:svRP: currProto previous guid" << currProto->protoGUID;
6995 DbgLv(1) << "EGUp:svRP: currProto previous protoname" << currProto->protoname;
6996 
6997  currProto->protoname = protoname; // Update current protocol
6998  if ( currProto->protoGUID.isEmpty() ||
6999  currProto->protoGUID.startsWith( "0000" ) )
7000  currProto->protoGUID = US_Util::new_guid(); // Get a new GUID
7001  else if ( old_protoname != protoname )
7002  currProto->protoGUID = US_Util::new_guid(); // Get a new GUID
7003 
7004 DbgLv(1) << "EGUp:svRP: currProto updated guid" << currProto->protoGUID;
7005 DbgLv(1) << "EGUp:svRP: currProto updated protoname" << currProto->protoname;
7006 
7007 
7008  // Now that we have protocol name,guid; save the Analysis Profile
7009  saveAnalysisProfile();
7010 
7011  // us_xml string has to be cleared each time Protocol is saved
7012  rpSubmt->us_xml.clear();
7013 
7014  QXmlStreamWriter xmlo( &rpSubmt->us_xml ); // Compose XML representation
7015  xmlo.setAutoFormatting( true );
7016  currProto->toXml( xmlo );
7017 
7018 
7019 DbgLv(1) << "EGUp:svRP: guid" << currProto->protoGUID;
7020 DbgLv(1) << "EGUp:svRP: xml(s)" << QString(rpSubmt->us_xml).left(100);
7021 int xe=rpSubmt->us_xml.length()-101;
7022 DbgLv(1) << "EGUp:svRP: xml(e)" << QString(rpSubmt->us_xml).mid(xe);
7023 
7024 
7025  // Save the new protocol to database and/or disk
7026  US_Passwd pw;
7027  US_DB2* dbP = ( sibSValue( "general", "dbdisk" ) == "DB" )
7028  ? new US_DB2( pw.getPasswd() ) : NULL;
7029  bool fromdisk = US_Settings::debug_match( "protocolFromDisk" );
7030  dbP = fromdisk ? NULL : dbP;
7031 
7032 DbgLv(1) << "EGUp:svRP: dbP" << dbP;
7033  // Always save the protocol to a local file
7034  int idProt = US_ProtocolUtil::write_record( rpSubmt->us_xml, NULL );
7035 
7036  // Usually (database selected), we write an additional record to DB
7037  if ( dbP != NULL )
7038  idProt = US_ProtocolUtil::write_record( rpSubmt->us_xml, dbP );
7039 
7040  if ( idProt < 0 )
7041  {
7042  QString errmsg = ( dbP != NULL ) ? dbP->lastError() : "???";
7043  QMessageBox::critical( this,
7044  tr( "*ERROR* in Protocol Write" ),
7045  tr( "An error occurred in the attempt to save"
7046  " new protocol\n %1\n %2 ." ).arg( protoname ).arg( errmsg ) );
7047 
7048  return save_aborted;
7049  }
7050 
7051  // Update the full list of existing protocols
7052  QStringList prentry; // New protocol summary data
7053  // QString pdate = US_Util::toUTCDatetimeText(
7054  // QDateTime::currentDateTime().toUTC()
7055  // .toString( "yyyy/MM/dd HH:mm" ), true );
7056  QString pdate = US_Util::toUTCDatetimeText(
7057  QDateTime::currentDateTime().toUTC()
7058  .toString( "yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm" ), true );
7059  // small bug fix above (UTC format, to be consistent with the format of existing records)
7060 
7061  QString protid = ( dbP != NULL ) ? QString::number( idProt )
7062  : "R" + QString().sprintf( "%7d", idProt ) + ".xml";
7063  QString pguid = currProto->protoGUID;
7064  prentry << protoname << pdate << protid << pguid;
7065 
7066  qDebug() << "Updated proto list: " << prentry;
7067 
7068  mainw->updateProtos( prentry ); // Update existing protocols list
7069  proto_svd = true;
7070  ck_prot_svd->setChecked( true );
7071 
7072  qDebug() << "constructor parms: mainw->automode, have_run -- " << mainw->automode << have_run;
7073 
7074  if ( mainw->automode && !have_run)
7075  {
7076  QString mtitle_done = tr( "Success" );
7077  QString message_done = tr( "Protocol has been successfully saved." );
7078  QMessageBox::information( this, mtitle_done, message_done );
7079  }
7080  else if ( !mainw->automode )
7081  {
7082  QString mtitle_done = tr( "Success" );
7083  QString message_done = tr( "Protocol has been successfully saved." );
7084  QMessageBox::information( this, mtitle_done, message_done );
7085  }
7086 
7087  return save_aborted;
7088 }

7090 // Slot to read all Optima machines <------------------------------- //
7091 void US_ExperGuiUpload::read_optima_machines( US_DB2* db )
7092 {
7093 
7094  all_instruments.clear();
7095 
7096  QStringList q( "" );
7097  q.clear();
7098  q << QString( "get_instrument_names" )
7099  << QString::number( 1 );
7100  db->query( q );
7101 
7102  if ( db->lastErrno() == US_DB2::OK ) // If not, no instruments defined
7103  {
7104  QList< int > instrumentIDs;
7105 
7106  // Grab all the IDs so we can reuse the db connection
7107  while ( db->next() )
7108  {
7109  int ID = db->value( 0 ).toString().toInt();
7110  instrumentIDs << ID;
7111 
7112  qDebug() << "InstID: " << ID;
7113  }
7114 
7115  // Instrument information
7116  foreach ( int ID, instrumentIDs )
7117  {
7118  QMap<QString,QString> instrument;
7119 
7120  q.clear();
7121  q << QString( "get_instrument_info_new" )
7122  << QString::number( ID );
7123  db->query( q );
7124  db->next();
7125 
7126  instrument[ "ID" ] = QString::number( ID );
7127  instrument[ "name" ] = db->value( 0 ).toString();
7128  instrument[ "serial" ] = db->value( 1 ).toString();
7129  instrument[ "optimaHost" ] = db->value( 5 ).toString();
7130  instrument[ "optimaPort" ] = db->value( 6 ).toString();
7131  instrument[ "optimaDBname" ] = db->value( 7 ).toString();
7132  instrument[ "optimaDBusername" ] = db->value( 8 ).toString();
7133  instrument[ "optimaDBpassw" ] = db->value( 9 ).toString();
7134  instrument[ "selected" ] = db->value( 10 ).toString();
7135 
7136  instrument[ "opsys1" ] = db->value( 11 ).toString();
7137  instrument[ "opsys2" ] = db->value( 12 ).toString();
7138  instrument[ "opsys3" ] = db->value( 13 ).toString();
7139 
7140  instrument[ "radcalwvl" ] = db->value( 14 ).toString();
7141  instrument[ "chromoab" ] = db->value( 15 ).toString();
7142 
7143  instrument[ "msgPort" ] = db->value( 16 ).toString();
7144 
7145  if ( instrument[ "name" ].contains("Optima") || instrument[ "optimaHost" ].contains("AUC_DATA_DB") )
7146  this->all_instruments << instrument;
7147  }
7148  }
7149  qDebug() << "Reading Instrument: FINISH in us_experiment: Upload";
7150 }

7715 //Read channel-to-ref_wvl info from AProfile
7716 bool US_ExperGuiUpload::readAProfileBasicParms( QXmlStreamReader& xmli, QMap<QString, QString>& channels_report )
7717 {
7718  channels_report. clear();
7719 
7720  while( ! xmli.atEnd() )
7721  {
7722  QString ename = xmli.name().toString();
7723 
7724  if ( xmli.isStartElement() )
7725  {
7726  if ( ename == "channel_parms" )
7727  {
7728  QXmlStreamAttributes attr = xmli.attributes();
7729 
7730  if ( attr.hasAttribute("load_volume") ) //ensure it reads upper-level <channel_parms>
7731  {
7732  //Channel Name
7733  QString channel_name = attr.value( "channel" ).toString();
7734 
7735  //Read what reportID corresponds to channel:
7736  if ( attr.hasAttribute("report_id") )
7737  channels_report[ channel_name ] = attr.value( "report_id" ).toString();
7738  }
7739  }
7740  }
7741 
7742  bool was_end = xmli.isEndElement(); // Just read was End of element?
7743  xmli.readNext(); // Read the next element
7744 
7745  if ( was_end && ename == "p_2dsa" ) // Break
7746  break;
7747  }
7748 
7749  return ( ! xmli.hasError() );
7750 }

7804  "&emsp; %1 <br><br>"
7805  "<b>Assigner Reviewer(s):</b> <br>"
7806  "&emsp; %2 <br><br>"
7807  "<b>Assigner Approver(s):</b> <br>"
7808  "&emsp; %3"))
7809  .arg( o_list )
7810  .arg( r_list )
7811  .arg( a_list );
7812 
7813 
7814  if ( o_list.contains( "MISSING" ) || r_list. contains( "MISSING") || a_list. contains( "MISSING") )
7815  {
7816  info_text += QString( tr( "<br><br> <font color='red'><b> ATTENTION: </b></font>"
7817  "Development run <b>can NOT</b> be submitted due to<br>"
7818  "missing assigned operator(s), reviewer(s) and/or approver(s).<br><br>"
7819  "Please return to 2. Labs/Rotor settings and provide missing information.")
7820  );
7821  }
7822  }
7823 
7824  msgBox.setInformativeText( info_text);
7825  msgBox.setWindowTitle(tr("Confirm Development Run Submission"));
7826 
7827  msgBox.setIcon(QMessageBox::Question);
7828  msgBox.exec();
7829 
7830  if (msgBox.clickedButton() == Accept)
7831  {
7832  if ( o_list.contains( "MISSING" ) || r_list. contains( "MISSING" ) || a_list. contains( "MISSING" ) )
7833  {
7834  return;
7835  }
7836  else
7837  {
7838  //get user info:
7839  //get info on logged in user [submitter]:
7840  US_Passwd pw;
7841  QString masterPW = pw.getPasswd();
7842  US_DB2 db( masterPW ); // New constructor
7843  QStringList qry;
7844  qry << QString( "get_user_info" );
7845  db. query( qry );
7846  db. next();
7847  int u_ID = db. value( 0 ).toInt();
7848  QString u_fname = db. value( 1 ).toString();
7849  QString u_lname = db. value( 2 ).toString();
7850  int u_lev = db. value( 5 ).toInt();
7851 
7852  QString user_submitter = u_lname + ", " + u_fname;
7853 
7854  //ask for submitter's credentials: password, comment [for subsequent audit trail]:
7855  qDebug() << "Checking master password...";
7856  gmp_submitter_map.clear();
7857  US_Passwd pw_at;
7858  gmp_submitter_map = pw_at.getPasswd_auditTrail( "GMP Run Submitter Form", "Please fill out GMP run submitter form:", user_submitter );
7859 
7860  int submit_map_size = gmp_submitter_map.keys().size();
7861  qDebug() << "Submitter map: "
7862  << gmp_submitter_map.keys() << gmp_submitter_map.keys().size() << submit_map_size
7863  << gmp_submitter_map.keys().isEmpty()
7864  << gmp_submitter_map[ "User:" ]
7865  << gmp_submitter_map[ "Comment:" ]
7866  << gmp_submitter_map[ "Master Password:" ];
7867 
7868  //Enable GMP run submit ONLY if form was filled && password correct
7869 
7870  if ( submit_map_size > 0 )
7871  {
7872  qDebug() << "Submitting [DEVELOPMENT] GMP...";
7873 
7874  //Warn user that ALL data (editPRofiles, model, noises, reports) will be deleted to this run
7875  QMessageBox msgBox_f;
7876  msgBox_f.setText(tr( "You are about to reinitialize the run based on the protocol:<br><br>" )
7877  + tr("<b>[OLD] Run Name:&emsp;</b>") + protocol_details[ "protocolName" ]
7878  + tr("<br>")
7879  + tr("<b>[NEW] Run Name:&emsp;</b>") + currProto->protoname
7880  + tr("<br>") );
7881 
7882  msgBox_f.setInformativeText( tr("<font color='red'><b>ATTENTION:</b></font> If you choose to Procceed, ")
7883  + tr("all existing edit profiles, models, and noises for this run will be deleted from DB, ")
7884  + tr("and the processing flow will reinitialize from the EDIT stage. ")
7885  + tr("<br><br><font color='red'><b>This action is not reversible. Proceed?</b></font>"));
7886 
7887  msgBox_f.setWindowTitle(tr("Run Reinitialization"));
7888  QPushButton *Confirm = msgBox_f.addButton(tr("Proceed"), QMessageBox::YesRole);
7889  QPushButton *Cancel = msgBox_f.addButton(tr("Cancel"), QMessageBox::RejectRole);
7890 
7891  msgBox_f.setIcon(QMessageBox::Question);
7892  msgBox_f.exec();
7893 
7894  if (msgBox_f.clickedButton() == Cancel)
7895  {
7896  return;
7897  }
7898  else if (msgBox_f.clickedButton() == Confirm)
7899  {
7900  //Clear data
7901  clearData_protDev();
7902  //qApp->processEvents();
7903 
7904  //Now procceed
7905  if ( have_run && rps_differ )
7906  {
7907  if ( saveRunProtocol() )
7908  return;
7909 
7910  //Now actually submit: make record in 'autoflow' table with 'DEV' flag
7911  submitExperiment_protDev();
7912  }
7913  }
7914  }
7915  }
7916  }
7917  else if (msgBox.clickedButton() == Cancel)
7918  {
7919  return;
7920  }
7921 }
